cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference universal-spawn in academic or industry work, please cite it using this metadata."
title: "universal-spawn: a declarative manifest standard for cross-platform spawning"
abstract: >-
  universal-spawn is an open specification for a single declarative
  manifest file (spawn.yaml) that makes any creation discoverable,
  validatable, and one-click spawnable across AI platforms, hosting
  providers, creative tools, dev ecosystems, games, social apps, and
  hardware. It defines a strict JSON Schema, a safety envelope
  (minimum permissions, rate ceilings, cost ceilings), and a
  registration model for platform-specific extensions.
